:{{DIcon}} I'd like to ask you something.
::'''Gouteng:''' Ask away! I can't chat long, though. I still have some matters to take care of.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502080003_68-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502080003_68-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why did you join the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus back then?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502080203-->
:::'''Gouteng:''' Mainly because there were too many restrictions around conducting research at the Alchemy Commission. I had to navigate layers and layers of red tape just to replicate some biotech processes and ancient prescriptions recorded in tomes. It's so bureaucratic!
:::'''Gouteng:''' But after I became a disciple, things became much less complicated. After I gained access to the underground connections afforded by the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus, even the approval process for taking time off work was much quicker!
:::'''Gouteng:''' I've turned over a new leaf since, though... No, really! My only goal now is to be an honest businessman alongside Arma and Shiratori. We'll grow the Correctional Group into as large and powerful a business as we possibly can!
:::'''Gouteng:''' When that happens, I may even be able to pick up where I left off and continue my research here at the Shackling Prison, hehehe.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What are your responsibilities as the Chief Technical R&D Officer?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502080208-->
:::'''Gouteng:''' Arma excels at making products that can greatly improve one's carceral quality of life out of the trash lying about in prison. While he's no doubt a deft hand at creating trinkets, that's really all that he's good at.
:::'''Gouteng:''' Not me, though. I'm an alchemist! Where you see kitchen scraps and trash, I see toothpaste, body wash, skincare products, and more. Where you see pests and irritants, I see medicines, supplements, snacks...
:::'''Gouteng:''' We have an abundance of raw materials in the Shackling Prison, but there's also an appalling lack of equipment and facilities here. Many things you wouldn't even take a second look at outside are rarities in here, and making these simple household chemical products is but child's play to me!
:::'''Gouteng:''' All I made in the beginning was toothpaste, but when Arma noticed what I did, he spotted a business opportunity and roped me into his venture.
:::'''Gouteng:''' Since then, I have developed many bestsellers for the Correctional Group, such as Immortal's Delight-flavored toothpaste, Flaming Tea-flavored hot sauce, instant mung bean soda...
:::'''Gouteng:''' I personally try out all my products, so rest assured I can attest to their quality! Of course, if your stomach does become upset, I can supply you with detoxification and anti-diarrheal medication on the house, hehe.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Is the business really your sole focus now?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502080215-->
:::'''Gouteng:''' You're perceptive, aren't you? Well, the answer is no. Since we only have one life to live, we shouldn't give up our hopes and dreams so easily, don't you think?
:::'''Gouteng:''' I'm an alchemist, after all. Even if I'm doomed to eternal confinement within the Shackling Prison, there's no way I'd be willing to resign myself to a lifetime of making household chemical products by hand.
:::'''Gouteng:''' I've been wondering... Perhaps certain academic conundrums can only be solved more easily if one is incarcerated in the Shackling Prison. For instance... the secrets of the Primus Immortus?
:::'''Gouteng:''' Oops, I might have said a bit too much. Can we pretend we never had this conversation? Hehe, thanks!
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} That's all from me. I'll leave you to work then.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502080220-->
:::'''Gouteng:''' Hehe, the Arma Correctional Group is glad to be of service!
